content: Hi. I have been a member of the call team for a number of weeks and have been making calls successfully. I did my shadow call shift and submitted my debrief form. I do not have access to any of the call team channels including the resource channel, the question channel and the main channel where announcements are made. I plan to continue making calls and would like to have access to these helpful resources. I am committed to being part of the call team and am respectful of all guidelines. If I have used a channel incorrectly, please let me know and I will abide by all additional information I receive. I am doing my best to be a good member of the call team and am unaware of any reason I should not have access to these channels, but if I have misunderstood how they are used please inform me and I will comply with any additional information you provide me with in response to this post. I reviewed a lot of information about how to use discord, the virtual office and its many channels and may have misinterpreted some of the information.

Hi Amy! I've tagged all call mods here so hopefully someone can help you with this. Also, be sure you click on "Team Harris-Walz Virtual Server" in top left sidebar and make sure "Show all Channels" is selected. Sometimes discord likes to glitch and turn that off even after we've selected it, so check first anytime channels disappear/aren't showing up for you!
They are showing up. They have been locked.
In that case, a call mod should be able to come along and help you here soon.
Thank you. I really appreciate your help.
<@456226577798135808> Are you looking for VOTE Team access?
I need access to the call team channels.
I did have access to at least one of them yesterday.
I see that you posted to <#1242256751445934262> this morning. Can you not see that channel any longer?
I can see the channel but I do not have access to see the resource channel and ask questions. My calls team channels have been locked. I can no longer post to any of them.
They have a lock symbol next to them.
I also see that you did your shadow shift as a Data Captain. Did you do your debrief form for that?
I did it for a Chat Captain. I did do my debrief form and I submitted it.
Yes, I meant Chat. Sorry.
So then you'll need both the Calls Team and the VOTE Team
No problem. I really appreciate your help!
Yes.
<@1257469301435400238> or <@1263159708466811000> Can you give <@456226577798135808> access to the Calls and Vote categories?
I have no access to them.
Thank you for contacting Frances Haydock and Eva Kwiatkowski. I have no way to access them.
I did DM Frances Haydock but I have not heard back.
We just need to give them some time to see this post.
<@1271505055589339207> - Can you give <@456226577798135808> access to Calls and Vote categories?
Thank you so much. I really appreciate the time and effort you took to help me.
I just added you to the vote team channels!
<@1257469301435400238> <@1271505055589339207> <@965992907981074443> I have the lock symbol next to those channels as well.  Is it that the DNC is now moderating them?
Not to my knowledge. I know that staff always had to add folks to the Vote team channels.
no--the lock symbol is standard symbol which means a channel is private (i.e. only open to a certain role)
so the locks on calls team are because calls team channels are private to only those with that role
Got it! Thanks.

I am a part of a member of the calls team and need access to the resources channel as well as the other channels. Also I now have the Vote Team channels locked although Frances you just said you gave me access. Thank you for continuing to help me.
<@456226577798135808> did you close out the app on your phone (shut it down completely, not just close it) and open it back up?
Ok I will try
Can you walk me through how to do that. I am making calls at 1:00 pm so I will do it after my call session. Can you DM me how to do that? I would really appreciate your help.
Sure- Let's move back to DMs
Thank you so much. I really appreciate how much you have helped me.

Of course! I'm sorry it's been frustrating. It's nice to have this technology to allow us to connect and have a broader impact, but it is definitely not perfect and can get pretty frustrating. Thanks for sticking with it.
I will stick with it! I really appreciate your help. I just sent you a DM. I really like making calls and want to take on a bigger role.
